SIMPLE: informant
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Informant
<hw>In*form"ant</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>informans</ets>, <ets>-antis</ets>, p. pr. of <ets>informare</ets>.
See <er>Inform</er>, <pos>v. t.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who,
or that which, informs, animates, or vivifies.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Glanvill.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One who imparts information or
instruction.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>One who offers an accusation; an informer. See
<er>Informer</er>.</def> <mark>[Obs. or R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>It was the last evidence of the kind; the <qex>informant</qex>⟦br⟧
was hanged.</q> <rj><qau>Burke.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Information</ent>⟦br⟧
